      "content": "I can certainly expand those sections. Under \"Permitted Use,\" the policy allows phones only for immediate family emergencies (like accidents or hospital visits) and safety alerts, requiring prior teacher approval for any other communication. For \"Prohibited Use,\" it explicitly bans all non-emergency functionality, including silent mode, volume-down, or hiding devices in pockets, desks, or clothing to evade detection. If a teacher discovers a phone being used surreptitiously, they must quietly confiscate it, document the incident, and confiscate the device for the remainder of the day without public shaming, with a follow-up meeting scheduled for the student to parent and the parent company to review the policy. This approach maintains order while addressing your concern about covert usage. Please have a legal professional review these specific clauses to ensure they meet local jurisdictional standards.",
